results.title: May You Live As Long As You Want And Never Want As Long As You Live - Irish Blessing - Vintage Book Art Print
results.description:
We love to give new life to old books with messages of hope, love and strength. We up-cycle the beautiful, weathered pages to create unique prints that glow with the patina of another age, so no two are alike. The result is a beautiful and interesting home decor print. Definitely a conversation starter!

Our prints are currently created using vintage books rescued from library recycling. Because of their age and condition, they may have flaws such as foxing (browning and spotting), nicked edges and the occasional corner turn. However, we feel these are desirable qualities, contributing to the inherent character of each print. 

The print(s) you purchase will be of the image you select, but the vintage book page it is printed on will be different. Every piece is an original work of art.

We offer two sizes of unframed prints, 5x7 and 8x10. They are both suitable for framing. They also come carefully packaged in a cellophane sleeve with a chipboard backing. Each print is shipped in a rigid chipboard mailer to ensure there is no damage during shipment. 

Please feel free to contact us if you have any questions. Your satisfaction is our goal.

We do offer custom orders as well as wholesale pricing to established businesses. Please contact us for more information.

All Rights Reserved.

Welcome to Decal Phanatics!

Payment Terms:
Paypal, Credit Cards, and Debit Cards

Installation: 
1. Clean application area. Use water (no Windex). Do not apply on extremely hot or cold surfaces.  
2. Prepare the decal by rubbing a credit card across the clear transfer tape
3. Peel the white paper backing off the sticker
4. Slowly place the decal onto the desired surface. Rub/Press decal firmly with credit card. 
5. Slowly peel the clear transfer tape off at from the top corner. Do not pull decal off while peeling transfer tape. 

Areas of Application: Car/Truck Windows, Car Body Surfaces, Bikes, Helmets, Motorcycles, Computers, Skateboards, Snowboards, Guitars, Mirrors, Laptops, Home Walls, Home Windows, Store Windows, Doors, Laminate, Boats, Toolboxes, etc.

results.title: SIGNS=WOOD | 'Live Well Laugh Often Love Much' | A Folk-Art Sign - Distressed
results.description:
SIGNS | 'LIVE WELL LAUGH OFTEN LOVE MUCH' | A FOLK-ART SIGN - DISTRESSED WOOD

Perfect for almost anywhere you want to send the very simple message that we all need to Live Laugh Love more, and focus on the 'good stuff' in life.

This is a simple, fun, light-weight, distressed wood sign, ... with a great message!

Feel-good home decor or ideal as a housewarming gift!

The wood source, for this sweet piece are 'paint sticks'. They are then secured in place via two sticks on the back side, with a strong adhesive. The stain throughout is a beautiful, rich, Dark Walnut.

It's ready to hang on the wall via a simple sawtooth mount, although it would be right at home on the mantle or standing up with a table-top easel as shown. The easel is not included.

This piece uses a transfer process for the lettering via a laser print. The distressing of the wood, on this piece happened before and after the lettering. This is not a vinyl-lettered, decal or sticker type item.

The process goes like this: staining assembly/adhesion >> drying/curing >> painting >> drying/curing >> distressing >> lettering via transfer process >> more painting >> drying/curing >> more distressing >> piece completed & signed >> piece ready to ship & be placed in shipping box >> end process.

Have you got a different idea altogether, in mind? A custom request? Send me a note. :) With a custom request, you can request any variation of stains, fonts, and color pallets.

Thanks for stopping by!

BethC :)
Find Your Joy & Follow Your Bliss
.
